messages.message:
Speaking of... One suggestion I put in the post-Atlanta survey was basically:
> As we discovered with this offsite, there's a power to getting people together in person.  And this effect is even stronger for collaborative events like a hackathon, as I've seen participating in both in-person and remote hackathons.  For the next/future hackathons, can we empower participants to be able to travel to meet up together as a team in an Instabase office to work together during the hackathon?
